column2: Date Denial Reason Code was received by NYCH+H EPIC system
Any billed CPT codes billed on the claim (only applicable for outpatient claims)
A number that identifies the type of facility, type of care, and sequence of the bill in the episode of care
Identification of the account (claim) in the system
Reimbursement NYCH+HC is expecting from payor based on the contracted rate for service and plan
Amount insurance will pay for service based on contracted rate for service and plan
Deductible: amount attributed to patient's cost sharing
Coinsurance: amount attributed to patient's cost sharing
Copay: amount attributed to patient's cost sharing
Date last a remittance was received from payor and posted in system
Determined by the patient's coverage- determines source of reimbursement
Number assigned the Insurance Payor (multiple for each insurnace based on financial class)
Number assigned to Insurance Payor Plan (multiple for each insurnace payor)
System categorization of the overall service of the encounter/visit
Principal Diagnosis Code: condition established after study to be chiefly responsible for the admission
Facility where patient is being treated
Denial Reason Code: Code retured by Payor which denotes denial
Description of the Denial Reason Code
Status of Denial record opened in system due to Denial reason code received
Date patient was seen at facility (for IP- date patient was admitted to hospital)
Date patient concluded service at facility (for IP- date patient was sent home or transferred from hospital)
Documented Length of Stay during an Inpatient Admission
The department that released patient from facility
